my:Hazard.my:ControlMeasures:
a) Permission must be obtained from the Master (as for all Enclosed Spaces); 
b) Safe Work Permit to be issued; 
c) All crew involved to be briefed and a contingency/rescue plan in place and understood by all; Rescue and resuscitation equipment has to be positioned at the entrance of the CO2 Room ready for use 
d) Prior to enter CO2 Room proper ventilation and illumination should be made. The atmosphere of the space should be tested with a properly calibrated oxygen meter before entering to ensure that acceptable level of oxygen is available. Ventilation should continue during the
period that the CO2 Room is occupied by crew. In the event of failure of the ventilation system, any person in the space should leave immediately;
e) The crew members who enter the CO2 Room should have an EEBD at all the times with them; 
f) A suitable system of communication between all parties during the entry should be available;

a) Crew to wear adequate PPE to existing temperatures in the CO2 Room (enclosed space); 
b) Use of ventilation at all the time; 
c) Breaks should be taken at regular intervals; 
d) Drink sufficient fluids (water) to avoid dehydration - Consumption of alcohol prohibited, soft drinks and coffee should be avoided; 
e) Where possible, all adjacent machinery should be stopped; 
f) Where possible, heating of adjacent compartments (i.e. fuel tank) should be stopped.
